## üî§ TYPOGRAPHY SYSTEM

### Font Families
- **Headlines & Titles**: `Georgia` (serif) - elegant, editorial feel
- **Body & UI**: System font (San Francisco) - clean, readable

### Font Hierarchy

```swift
// Navigation Title / Brand Name
.font(.custom("Georgia", size: 22))
.fontWeight(.medium)
.tracking(6)

// Section Headlines (H1)
.font(.custom("Georgia", size: 36))
.fontWeight(.regular)
.lineSpacing(4)

// Section Headers (H2)
.font(.custom("Georgia", size: 24))
.fontWeight(.medium)
.tracking(4)

// Subsection Headers (H3)
.font(.custom("Georgia", size: 20))
.fontWeight(.medium)
.tracking(2)

// Category Labels / Badges
.font(.custom("Georgia", size: 13))
.fontWeight(.medium)
.tracking(3)

// Small Labels / Tags
.font(.system(size: 11, weight: .medium))
.tracking(1.5)

// Body Text
.font(.system(size: 15))

// Caption / Subtitle
.font(.system(size: 13))

// Micro Text (badges, tags)
.font(.system(size: 10, weight: .semibold))
.tracking(3)

// Button Text
.font(.system(size: 13, weight: .semibold))
.tracking(2)
```

### Typography Rules
- Use `.tracking()` (letter-spacing) on uppercase text for elegance
- Headlines often use line breaks for dramatic effect
- Avoid bold weights on serif fonts - use regular or medium
- Product names: `.font(.system(size: 14))` single line
- Brand names: UPPERCASE with tracking
- Prices: `.font(.system(size: 14, weight: .semibold))`

