## ‚ú® ANIMATION GUIDELINES

### Entrance Animations

```swift
// Staggered list entrance
ForEach(Array(items.enumerated()), id: \.element.id) { index, item in
    ItemView(item: item)
        .opacity(hasAppeared ? 1 : 0)
        .offset(y: hasAppeared ? 0 : 20)
        .animation(
            .spring(response: 0.6, dampingFraction: 0.8)
            .delay(Double(index) * 0.1),
            value: hasAppeared
        )
}

// Section fade in
.opacity(hasAppeared ? 1 : 0)
.animation(.easeOut(duration: 0.8).delay(0.5), value: hasAppeared)
```

### Interactive Animations

```swift
// Press state
@State private var isPressed = false

.scaleEffect(isPressed ? 0.95 : 1.0)
.animation(.spring(response: 0.3), value: isPressed)
.onLongPressGesture(minimumDuration: .infinity, pressing: { pressing in
    isPressed = pressing
}, perform: {})
```

### Animation Rules
- Use `.spring(response: 0.6, dampingFraction: 0.8)` for natural feel
- Stagger delays: 0.08-0.1 seconds between items
- Keep animations subtle (20-30pt offset, not 50+)
- Fade + translate for entrances
- Scale for press states (0.95-0.98)
- Duration 0.3-0.8 seconds max

